1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:18,000
Professional lighting tools exist, but reaching the first visual answer
can require CAD knowledge and hours of setup.

2
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Import a floor plan, set one known dimension, and trace only enough
of the home to judge lighting in context.

3
00:00:45,000 --> 00:01:17,000
Place a fixture, move it, and immediately change brightness,
color temperature, fixture type, beam distribution, and aiming.

4
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:43,000
2D keeps placement clear. Fast 3D gives immediate feedback.
Realistic mode adds progressive direct and indirect lighting when supported.

5
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:58,000
Export a watermarked PNG, autosave locally,
or save the editable project as JSON.

6
00:01:58,000 --> 00:02:12,000
Use the workflow in Japanese or English,
with compact 2D, 3D, and editing controls on a phone.

7
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Codex with GPT-5.6 inspected and hardened the existing app,
implemented the bilingual UI, validated it, and prepared the documentation.

8
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:45,000
Professional CAD is built for specialists.
LDK Lighting Lab lets anyone try a lighting idea in their own home.
